# Profile Help

## What is a Profile?

A Profile tells AuraTxt how to communicate with a specific AI model
family — in particular, how to turn "thinking mode" on or off, and
whether to strip reasoning tags (<think>...</think>) from the output.

Different providers use completely different JSON fields for this.
Profiles handle the translation automatically, so you just set
ThinkingMode = "disable" or "enable_high" on an action and the
correct payload is sent to whichever model you are using.

## How auto-matching works

When a model's Profile is set to "(auto)", AuraTxt picks the best
profile by matching the model's full name against each profile's
name patterns (glob, case-insensitive, * = wildcard), in priority
order (highest number wins). If nothing matches, it falls back to
a safe default that sends no thinking-control payload at all.

Examples:

  deepseek-ai/deepseek-v4-flash   matches  deepseek-v4    (priority 90)
  meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct     matches  llama-nemotron (priority 80)
  gemini-2.5-flash-preview        matches  gemini-flash   (priority 90)
  qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-instruct matches qwen3-next-instruct (priority 100)
  unknown-new-model               falls back to default-openai

You almost never need to change a model's profile manually. Auto is
correct in the vast majority of cases. Only override it if the wrong
profile is being picked — use "auracfg profile --probe" to check.

## Example 1 — DeepSeek V4 on NIM (openai_compatible)

Profile: deepseek-v4
ThinkingMode "disable"   → adds to request body:
  "chat_template_kwargs": { "thinking": false, "enable_thinking": false }
ThinkingMode "enable_high" → adds:
  "chat_template_kwargs": { "thinking": true, "reasoning_effort": "high" }

## Example 2 — Gemini 2.5 Flash (gemini_native)

Profile: gemini-flash
ThinkingMode "disable"   → adds to request body:
  "generationConfig": { "thinkingConfig": { "thinkingBudget": 0 } }
ThinkingMode "enable_high" → adds:
  "generationConfig": { "thinkingConfig": { "thinkingBudget": 8192 } }

## When to set a profile manually

  - A brand-new model isn't recognized and falls back to default
  - You created a custom profile in this folder and want to pin it
  - Auto picks the wrong profile (verify with --probe, then override)

## Troubleshooting

  Thinking not disabled  →  wrong profile or wrong payload
                             run: auracfg profile --probe --provider P --model M

  400 error from Gemini  →  model doesn't support thinkingConfig
                             try profile: gemini-legacy  (thinking: null)

  Wrong profile matched  →  raise its priority, or tighten name_patterns

## Managing Profiles

  List all:        auracfg profile --list
  Inspect one:     auracfg profile --show --id deepseek-v4
  Probe live:      auracfg profile --probe --provider nim --model deepseek-ai/deepseek-v4-flash
  Add custom:      auracfg profile --new  (interactive wizard)
  Validate file:   auracfg profile --validate profiles/my-model.json
